    </h2>
    <div id="publications" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
      <div class="accordion-body">
        <strong>List of refereed works (mostly articles accepted in a peer-review journal). </strong>
        They are grouped by themes and choronological order.
        The corresponding talks are collected in the following rubrick.
        I welcome (m)any discussions about those topics, and you are welcome to contact me to exchange about them.
      </div>
    
          <ul>
            <li> <i> On the topology of a real analytic curve in the neighborhood of a singular point </i> <br>
               Work in collaboration with <a href=https://perso.ens-lyon.fr/ghys/accueil/> Etienne Ghys</a>.<br>
               Journal <a href=https://smf.emath.fr/publications/sur-la-topologie-des-courbes-analytiques-reelles-au-voisinage-des-points-singuliers> link</a>.
               HAL <a href=https://hal.science/hal-03273688> link </a>.
               Preprint <a href="pre-publications/2017-04_TopoSingulaReAnalytiCurve_ghysimon.pdf"> version</a>.
            </li>
            
            <li> <i> Topologie et dénombrement des courbes algébriques réelles singulières </i> <br>
               Journal <a href=https://afst.centre-mersenne.org/articles/10.5802/afst.1698/> link</a>.
               HAL <a href="HALINKHERE"> link</a>.
               ArXiv <a href=https://arxiv.org/abs/2106.15450> link</a>.
            </li>
            
            <li> <i> Automorphisms of character varieties </i> <br>
               Work in collaboration with <a href=https://webusers.imj-prg.fr/~julien.marche/travaux_publis.html> Julien Marché</a>.<br>
               Journal <a href=https://ahl.centre-mersenne.org/item/10.5802/ahl.82.pdf> link.</a>
               Numdam <a href=http://www.numdam.org/articles/10.5802/ahl.82/> link.</a>
               HAL <a href="HALINKHERE"> link</a>.
               ArXiv <a href=https://arxiv.org/abs/1909.12539> link</a>.
            </li>
            
            <li> <i> Valuations on the character variety: Newton polytopes and Residual Poisson Bracket </i> <br>
               Work in collaboration with <a href=https://webusers.imj-prg.fr/~julien.marche/travaux_publis.html> Julien Marché</a>.<br>
               Journal : <a href=https://msp.org/soon/coming.php?jpath=gt> link</a> to appear.
               Numdam : <a href=http://www.numdam.org/articles/10.5802/ahl.82/> link</a>.
               HAL <a href="HALINKHERE"> link</a>.
               ArXiv : <a href=https://arxiv.org/abs/2104.04340> link</a>.
            </li>
            
            <li> <i> Arithmetic and topology of modular knots </i> <br>
               PhD Thesis, under the direction 
               of <a href=https://perso.ens-lyon.fr/ghys/accueil/> Etienne Ghys</a>
               and <a href=http://math.univ-lille1.fr/~popescu/> Patrick Popescu-Pampu</a>.<br>
               A compressed <a href="pre-publications/2022-07-14_AriTopoModuKnots_compressed"> manuscript </a> and the
               HAL <a href=https://theses.hal.science/tel-03755147v1> link</a>. <br>
               The introduction gives an idea of the motivations, and each chapter is preceded by a short introduction. <br>
               The "Appetizer" section to the introduction served as basis 
               for my <a href="talkslides/2022-06-24_SouThese_AriTopoNoeMod.pdf"> oral defense</a>. <br>
               Warning : several of the results and conjectures have been (im)proved in the following papers.
            </li>
            
            <li> <i> Conjugacy classes in PSL(2;Z) </i> <br>
               This article synthetises and extends the results in chapter 1 of my thesis. <br>
               Journal : <a href=> link</a> to appear.
               ArXiv <a href=https://arxiv.org/abs/2210.02481> link</a>. 
            </li>
            
            <li> <i> Linking numbers of modular knots </i> <br>
               This article synthetises and extends the results in chapter 4 and 5. <br>
               Submitted for publication.
               ArXiv <a href=https://arxiv.org/abs/2211.05957> link</a>. 
            </li>
         </ul>
